milestone.title: Docs Only
milestone.description:
Documentation only pull requests and issues can go in here.

This is a place to put PRs that are purely updating the documentation - i.e. no code changes.

When triaging I was putting such PRs into the next milestone, which at the moment would be 1.2.2 but I found that since these doc-fixes were not blocking releases, it was hiding how much real work was needed before the milestone was ready for the release.  

In effect, I created a parallel track for documentation updates.  Then when I had the time, I could sit down and knock off a dozen of these PRs at my leisure.

title: docs(ngShowHide): update example in description
body:
To remove or to add ng-hide class only depends on the boolean value of ngShow/ngHide property. 
So the initial state of ng-hide class does not affect the visibility.

Use ng-show and ng-hide respectively.

title: Add expire date to cookies
body:
Cookies are supposed to be persistent storage so we want them to live as
long as possible.

title: fix($resource): Always return a resource instance when calling class met...
body:
...hods on resources.

Previously, calling `MyResource.save(myResourceInstance)`returned
a promise, in contrast to the docs for `$resource`. However,
calling `MyResource.save({name: 'Tobias"})`already correctly
returned a resource instance.

Fixes #4545.

title: feat($browser): add expires to cookies() method
body: This PR add a new optional parameter to the cookies() method to allow the expire date to be explicit. Please note the test cannot check the expire date so the only way to test is to check its validity if its set in the past or in the future. If you have a better idea on how to test it I can improve it.

title: fix(loader): expose `$$minErr` to modules such as`ngResource`
body:
This is highlighted in angular-phonecat when you try to use the index-async.html
which needs to load the ngResource module asynchronously but fails when it tries
to call `angular.$$minErr` to create the $resourceMinErr object.

This will finally solve the issues blocking https://github.com/angular/angular-phonecat/pull/90

title: fix(angular.encodeUriSegment): do not encode semi-colon
body:
RFC 3986 indicates that ; is not encoded as part of the URI, as is the case
with other members of sub-delim. Changed encodeUriSegment to match that
behaviour, along with the corresponding spec.

This was causing a practical issue with Java servers that append `;jsessionid=...` to the path. The `;` was encoded, leading to the following error in PhantomJS as it continually saw the current URL as different to the `$location.absUrl()` which had been encoded:

```
Error: [$rootScope:infdig] 10 $digest() iterations reached. Aborting!
Watchers fired in the last 5 iterations: [["fn: $locationWatch; newVal: 7; oldVal: 6"],["fn: $locationWatch; newVal: 8; oldVal: 7"],["fn: $locationWatch; newVal: 9; oldVal: 8"],["fn: $locationWatch; newVal: 10; oldVal: 9"],["fn: $locationWatch; newVal: 11; oldVal: 10"]]
```

I note that the specs previously called out `;` specifically for being encoded, which was introduced in 9e30baad3feafc82fb2f2011fd3f21909f4ba29e, and that it has been in place for some time. Is there a reason this might have been needed that I've missed?

I also note that the same code is in `ngResource`, but I'm unfamiliar with the codebase and what impact it would have to change that as well. Should the code in there be updated as well?

title: $http cache returning a promise
body:
First stab at adding support for cache factories that return promises. The motivation for this was adding support for using IndexedDB as a backend of the cache factory when most operations on it are asynchronous and must therefore return promises.

I'm not completely happy with the duplication of code in the callback. Also, the mocking of the cache factory may not be the best practice. Feedback appreciated ).
